phases.content:
Add a status-aware primary action button to `apps/desktop/src/components/sidebar/WorkProgressCard.tsx`. One click switches the center view to Terminal, activates the work's associated terminal tab (or creates one), and writes the next-step tiki command via the existing `invoke("write_terminal", ...)` pattern that `App.tsx:441` already uses.

### Scope: IssueWork only this phase

The issue's acceptance criteria mention both IssueWork and ReleaseWork, but the existing action buttons (Pause/Reset/Remove) are already gated on `isIssue` (line 209). Match that — release-card semantics for resume aren't well-defined (re-run the release? next issue? both have open design questions). Gating Release out keeps this an S-effort change consistent with the issue's effort rating. If we later need a release-level Resume, it earns its own follow-up issue.

### Helper: pure status → action mapper (module scope, above the component)

```ts
type ResumeAction = { label: string; command: string };

/**
 * Derive the next-step action for an issue from its current pipeline state.
 * Returns null when no resume action is meaningful (e.g. completed) or the
 * issue is actively executing (the disable predicate also covers that).
 */
function getResumeAction(
  status: WorkStatus,
  pipelineStep: PipelineStep | undefined,
  issueNumber: number
): ResumeAction | null {
  switch (status) {
    case "pending":
      return { label: "Start", command: `/tiki:get ${issueNumber}` };
    case "reviewing":
    case "planning":
      // Map by pipelineStep when present so AUDIT can resume into PLAN/AUDIT correctly.
      if (pipelineStep === "AUDIT") return { label: "Continue Audit", command: `/tiki:audit ${issueNumber}` };
      return { label: "Continue Planning", command: `/tiki:plan ${issueNumber}` };
    case "executing":
    case "paused":
      return { label: "Resume", command: `/tiki:execute ${issueNumber}` };
    case "failed":
      // No stored last-command; pick by pipelineStep, fall back to execute.
      if (pipelineStep === "GET") return { label: "Retry", command: `/tiki:get ${issueNumber}` };
      if (pipelineStep === "PLAN") return { label: "Retry", command: `/tiki:plan ${issueNumber}` };
      if (pipelineStep === "AUDIT") return { label: "Retry", command: `/tiki:audit ${issueNumber}` };
      if (pipelineStep === "SHIP") return { label: "Retry Ship", command: `/tiki:ship ${issueNumber}` };
      return { label: "Retry", command: `/tiki:execute ${issueNumber}` };
    case "shipping":
      return { label: "Ship", command: `/tiki:ship ${issueNumber}` };
    case "completed":
      return null;
    default:
      return null;
  }
}
```

Reuse the existing `WorkStatus` and `PipelineStep` types already imported/declared in the file (no new type definitions).

### Store subscriptions (add inside the component, near existing selectors)

Guarded on `isIssue` (issueNumber !== undefined):
```tsx
const projectTabs = useTerminalStore((s) => projectId ? s.tabsByProject[projectId] ?? [] : []);
const workTerminalMap = useTerminalStore((s) => projectId ? s.terminalByWorkIdByProject[projectId] ?? {} : {});
```
Mirror the exact pattern from `IssueDetail.tsx` lines 143–146.

### Handler: `handleResume`

```tsx
const resumeAction =
  issueNumber !== undefined
    ? getResumeAction(work.status, work.pipelineStep, issueNumber)
    : null;
const isActivelyRunning = work.status === "executing" && phaseStatus === "executing";
const resumeDisabled = resumeAction === null || isActivelyRunning;

const handleResume = async (e: React.MouseEvent) => {
  e.stopPropagation();
  if (resumeDisabled || !resumeAction || issueNumber === undefined || !projectId) return;

  // Switch view to Terminal regardless of association state.
  useLayoutStore.getState().setActiveView("terminal");

  const jumpTarget = resolveWorkTerminal(workTerminalMap, projectTabs, issueNumber);
  if (jumpTarget === null) {
    // No terminal associated yet — create one, record the association, surface a toast.
    // Skip the write this click: the PTY won't be ready synchronously, and trying to time
    // it adds fragility. Second click resolves cleanly via the now-recorded association.
    const newTabId = useTerminalStore.getState().addTab(projectId);
    useTerminalStore.getState().associateWorkTerminal(issueNumber, newTabId);
    useTerminalStore.getState().setActiveTab(projectId, newTabId);
    useToastStore.getState().addToast({
      type: "info",
      message: `Opened a new terminal for issue #${issueNumber}. Click ${resumeAction.label} again to send the command.`,
    });
    return;
  }

  // Terminal already associated — activate the tab and write the command immediately.
  useTerminalStore.getState().setActiveTab(jumpTarget.projectId, jumpTarget.tabId);
  await invoke("write_terminal", {
    id: jumpTarget.terminalId,
    data: `${resumeAction.command}\r`,
  });
  terminalFocusRegistry.focus(jumpTarget.terminalId);
};
```

Imports needed at top of file:
- `import { invoke } from "@tauri-apps/api/core";`
- `import { useToastStore } from "../../stores";` (if not already)
- `import { useLayoutStore } from "../../stores";` (if not already)
- `import { useTerminalStore, resolveWorkTerminal } from "../../stores/terminalStore";` (or whatever the existing barrel resolves to — check `IssueDetail.tsx`)
- `import { terminalFocusRegistry } from "../../utils/terminalFocusRegistry";` (path per `IssueDetail.tsx`)

Reuse rather than reinvent — every dependency already exists.

### JSX placement

In the action-button row (around line 209 where Pause/Reset/Remove live), render the Resume button as the **first/leftmost** button when `isIssue && !showConfirmRemove && resumeAction !== null`:

```tsx
<button
  type="button"
  className="work-action-btn work-action-btn--primary"
  onClick={handleResume}
  disabled={resumeDisabled}
  title={resumeAction ? `Sends "${resumeAction.command}" to the issue's terminal` : undefined}
>
  {resumeAction.label}
</button>
```

### CSS — `WorkProgressCard.css` (add a new primary variant)

```css
.work-action-btn--primary {
  background-color: var(--accent-color);
  color: #fff;
  border-color: var(--accent-color);
}
.work-action-btn--primary:hover:not(:disabled) {
  background-color: var(--accent-hover);
  border-color: var(--accent-hover);
}
.work-action-btn--primary:disabled {
  opacity: 0.5;
  cursor: not-allowed;
}
```

Keep the existing `.work-action-btn` rule untouched — the primary class composes on top.

### Discriminated-union narrowing

Per CLAUDE.md's TypeScript gotcha, narrow via *direct ternary* not intermediate booleans. `issueNumber` is already extracted that way in the component (line 62) — reuse it; pass `issueNumber` (which is `number | undefined`) directly into `getResumeAction` after the `!== undefined` guard.

### Scope boundaries

- Two files: `WorkProgressCard.tsx` + `WorkProgressCard.css`.
- No Rust, no IPC additions (uses the existing `write_terminal` command), no state-shape changes.
- Pure additive — no existing behavior changes.
- Release work cards: button not rendered (`isIssue` gate). Documented as a known limitation; future enhancement.
- No new dependency on a phase-status enum — uses the existing `phaseStatus` local already computed at line 94.

### Test plan

- `pnpm build` — clean tsc -b + vite build. Watch for unused imports per the v0.5.4 TS6133 regret.
- `pnpm test` — desktop vitest 89 baseline preserved.
- Manual smoke (developer): (a) Open an issue in pending state → see "Start" button, click → terminal view + new tab + toast; click again → command sent; (b) Open a paused-mid-execute issue → see "Resume", click → terminal jumps + command sent; (c) Open an actively-executing issue → button disabled; (d) Open a completed issue → no button; (e) Open a release card → no button (release gate).
